OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA bright start, with a few
OL,6,Fblustery showers. It should become dry
OL,7,Ffor a while in the morning, though
OL,8,Frain will arrive from the southwest
OL,9,Flater with a damp afternoon following.
OL,10,FSome fog patches developing. Mild,
OL,11,Fthough remaining breezy.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FIt will be a cloudy evening
OL,14,Fwith some rain and fog patches in
OL,15,Fplaces. Turning drier overnight,
OL,16,Fthough staying rather cloudy. It will
OL,17,Fbe mild, and fairly breezy.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
